Argued June 18, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. THEODORE SEYMOUR, Appellant. (No. 72 1496) 510 P2d 1336 J. Marvin Kuhn, Deputy Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause for appellant. With him on the brief was Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem. John W. Burgess, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osbnrn, Solicitor General, Salem.

affirmed June 18,

petition for rehearing denied July 11,

petition for review denied September 18, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Langtry and Port, Judges.
